Fixed Width: Blocks of content will be the same fixed width.
Launching fixed width on small screen : site will zoom out, or render at fixed resolution, possibly ruinign the ux.
Fluid Layout, Liquid Layout: define space and width percentages
Height, Width, Margin, and Padding percentages

Media Queries: retrieve device information in CSS
@ media only screen and (min-width: 768px)
@ media only screen and (max width: 320px) and (min-width: 320px)
ex. unfloat elements in media query:
@media only screen and (max-width: 480px) {
    .article {
        float: none;
        width: auto;
    }
}

Adaptive Design
developers set media queries at widths responding to specific devices in portrait and landscape

Em
A unit of measurement used in typography
defined by width of uppercase M in the current face and point size

Set body font-size to 30px and in media queries, alter body to lower font sizes

Media Queries
screens (max width: 768px) ipad in portrait... align headings to center, unfloat Blocks
screens (max-wdith: 480px) iphones in landscape
set wrapper to 95%, more real estate
add meta tag in head - site assumes device it's looking at

Viewport: width of screen
all mobile devices have two orientations
We typically set two breakpoints. one for tablets (portrait and landscape)
and one for portrait oriented small screens

make images links, link goes to image
